712074f-a.title: Manhattan: 33rd Street (West) - 11th Avenue
712074f-a.text:
West 33rd 3treet, south side, at Eleventh Avenue, show-
the New York Central Railroad yards and the Eleventh Ave.
ramp being carried across same. Fringing the southerly
side of this extensive transportation locale, is the ele-
vated roadbed that carries these trains southward to the
St. John's Freight Depot, downtown. The buildings beyond
are to the south of West 30th Street. The white utili-
tarian feature at the left is the new U. S. Parcel Post
Bldg. on Ninth and Tenth Avenues. This replaced the old
Milk Depot. On the riht margin appears a substantial part
of the outstanding Starett-Lehigh Bldg. extending between
Eleventh and Thirteenth Avenue's.
August 24, 1940
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPROUUTTIONS
